                             │\n│  New Normalized Tables:                                         │\n│    sops ─┬─ sop_sections (typed, with REF pointers)            │\n│          ├─ sop_steps (unified, phase-aware)                   │\n│          ├─ sop_dependencies (cross-reference graph)           │\n│          └─ sop_ref_docs (shared trade references)             │\n│                                                                 │\n│  WO Integration:                                                │\n│    work_orders ──► work_order_step_progress ◄── sop_steps      │\n└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n```\n\n---\n\n## Database Tables\n\n### Core Table: `sops`\n\nMaster SOP record with metadata, storage path, and file hash.\n\n| Column | Type | Description |\n|---|---|---|\n| `id` | uuid | Primary key |\n| `sop_number` | text | Unique identifier (e.g., `PNT-SOP-001`) |\n| `trade_code` | text | Trade abbreviation (e.g., `PNT`, `PLB`) |\n| `trade_name` | text | Full trade name |\n| `task_name` | text | Task description |\n| `revision` | text | Version number |\n| `status` | text | `active`, `draft`, `archived` |\n| `storage_path` | text | Supabase Storage path |\n| `file_hash` | text | MD5 hash for change detection |\n| `ref_doc_id` | uuid | FK to `sop_ref_docs` (auto-linked by trade) |\n| `tags` | text[] | Searchable tags |\n\n### New Table: `sop_sections`\n\nNormalized section-level content with type classification.\n\n| Column | Type | Description |\n|---|---|---|\n| `id` | uuid | Primary key |\n| `sop_id` | uuid | FK to `sops` |\n| `section_number` | int | Section order (1-16) |\n| `section_type` | text | Classified type (see below) |\n| `title` | text | Original section title |\n| `content_md` | text | Raw markdown content |\n| `content_plain` | text | Stripped plain text |\n| `is_ref_pointer` | bool | `true` if section delegates to REF doc |\n| `ref_section` | text | Referenced section in REF doc |\n| `phase_name` | text | Phase name (procedure sections only) |\n\n**Section Types:**\n`purpose`, `scope`, `references`, `personnel`, `safety`, `tools`, `pre_work`, `procedure`, `videos`, `testing`, `cleanup`, `troubleshooting`, `quality`, `revision_history`\n\n### New Table: `sop_steps`\n\nUnified step records merging Executive Checklist + Detailed Steps.\n\n| Column | Type | Description |\n|---|---|---|\n| `id` | uuid | Primary key |\n| `sop_id` | uuid | FK to `sops` |\n| `section_id` | uuid | FK to `sop_sections` |\n| `phase_name` | text | Phase name (e.g., \"Surface Preparation\") |\n| `phase_number` | int | Phase sequence number |\n| `step_number` | int | Step number within phase |\n| `step_name` | text | Step title |\n| `tasks_summary` | text | One-line task summary (from checklist) |\n| `detail_md` | text | Full detailed step content (markdown) |\n| `detail_plain` | text | Plain text version |\n| `sort_order` | int | Global sort order |\n\n### New Table: `sop_dependencies`\n\nCross-reference graph between SOPs extracted from Scope sections.\n\n| Column | Type | Description |\n|---|---|---|\n| `id` | uuid | Primary key |\n| `from_sop_id` | uuid | FK to `sops` — the SOP containing the reference |\n| `to_sop_id` | uuid | FK to `sops` — the referenced SOP |\n| `link_type` | text | `cross_reference`, `prerequisite`, `related` |\n| `condition_note` | text | Context (e.g., task name of referenced SOP) |\n\n**Dependency patterns detected:**\n```\n(see PNT-SOP-004: Trim & Baseboard Painting)   → with title\n(see SOP PLB-SOP-010)                           → without title\n(see ELC-SOP-005: New Branch Circuit)           → cross-trade\n(see CRP-SOP-001: Interior Door Replacement)    → cross-trade with title\n```\n\n### New Table: `sop_ref_docs`\n\nShared reference documents per trade (codes, standards, qualifications).\n\n| Column | Type | Description |\n|---|---|---|\n| `id` | uuid | Primary key |\n| `doc_id` | text | Unique document ID (e.g., `REF-PNT-001`) |\n| `trade_code` | text | Trade abbreviation |\n| `trade_name` | text | Full trade name |\n| `trade_id` | uuid | FK to `trades` table (if exists) |\n| `revision` | text | Document revision |\n| `content_md` | text | Full markdown content |\n| `storage_path` | text | Supabase Storage path |\n| `file_hash` | text | MD5 hash for change detection |\n\n### Legacy Tables (still maintained)\n\n- `sop_executive_checklists` — Flat checklist items per phase\n- `sop_detailed_steps` — Detailed step content per phase\n- `sop_recommended_videos` — Video references per phase\n- `sop_sync_log` — Audit log of all sync operations\n\n---\n\n## Parsing Functions\n\n### `parse_to_sections_and_steps()`\n\nParses an SOP markdown file into structured data for `sop_sections` and `sop_steps` tables.\n\n**Handles:**\n- **Section header detection**: `## N. Title` → section_number + title\n- **Section type classification**: Title keywords mapped to enum values\n- **REF pointer detection**: `See [REF_...` at section start → `is_ref_pointer=true`\n- **Executive Checklist parsing**: Pipe-delimited `| Step | Step Name | Tasks | ✓ |` tables\n- **Detailed Steps extraction**: `#### Step N: Name` subsections\n- **Phase name extraction**: `Procedure — Phase Name` → `phase_name`\n\n**Returns:**\n```python\n{\n    \"sections\": [\n        {\n            \"section_number\": 8,\n            \"section_type\": \"procedure\",\n            \"title\": \"Procedure — Surface Preparation\",\n            \"content_md\": \"...\",\n            \"content_plain\": \"...\",\n            \"is_ref_pointer\": False,\n            \"ref_section\": None,\n            \"phase_name\": \"Surface Preparation\"\n        }\n    ],\n    \"steps\": [\n        {\n            \"_section_number\": 8,\n            \"phase_name\": \"Surface Preparation\",\n            \"phase_number\": 1,\n            \"step_number\": 1,\n            \"step_name\": \"Clear & Protect the Space\",\n            \"tasks_summary\": \"Move or cover furniture; lay drop cloths...\",\n            \"detail_md\": \"...\",\n            \"detail_plain\": \"...\",\n            \"sort_order\": 1\n        }\n    ]\n}\n```\n\n### `parse_scope_dependencies()`\n\nExtracts SOP cross-references from the Scope section.\n\n**Detects patterns:**\n```\n(see PNT-SOP-004: Trim & Baseboard Painting)\n(see SOP PLB-SOP-010)\nsee DRW-SOP-001: Drywall Patch Repair\n(see ELC-SOP-005: New Branch Circuit Installation)\n```\n\n**Returns:**\n```python\n[\n    {\"to_sop_number\": \"PNT-SOP-004\", \"condition_note\": \"Trim & Baseboard Painting\"},\n    {\"to_sop_number\": \"DRW-SOP-001\", \"condition_note\": \"Drywall Patch Repair\"}\n]\n```\n\n### `REFDocParser.parse()`\n\nParses `REF_{TRADE}_Codes_Standards.md` files into `sop_ref_docs` records.\n\n**Extracts:**\n- `doc_id` from header table (e.g., `REF-PNT-001`)\n- `trade_code` from doc_id (e.g., `PNT`)\n- `trade_name` from document title\n- `revision` from header table\n- Full `content_md` with `file_hash`\n\n---\n\n## CLI Commands\n\n### Existing Commands\n\n```bash\n# Upload SOP to storage + parse + sync all tables\npython sop_manager.py upload <file.md>\n\n# Re-sync legacy tables from storage\npython sop_manager.py sync --all\npython sop_manager.py sync <SOP_NUMBER>\n\n# Search SOPs by keyword\npython sop_manager.py search <query>\n\n# List all SOPs\npython sop_manager.py list\n\n# Show SOP details (all tables)\npython sop_manager.py show <SOP_NUMBER>\n\n# Check if SOP exists, request creation if not\npython sop_manager.py check <trade> <task>\n\n# Request agent to create a new SOP\npython sop_manager.py request <trade> <task>\n```\n\n### New Commands\n\n```bash\n# Sync to new normalized schema (sop_sections + sop_steps)\npython sop_manager.py sync-new --all\npython sop_manager.py sync-new <SOP_NUMBER>\n\n# Upload REF doc to sop_ref_docs + auto-link matching SOPs\npython sop_manager.py upload-ref <REF_file.md>\n\n# Extract and sync SOP dependencies from Scope sections\npython sop_manager.py sync-deps --all\npython sop_manager.py sync-deps <SOP_NUMBER>\n```\n\n---\n\n## REF Document Management\n\nREF (Reference) documents contain shared trade-level content:\n- Codes & Standards references\n- Personnel & Qualifications requirements\n- Standard PPE requirements\n- Common Hazard Awareness tables\n\n### REF Doc Workflow\n\n1. **Author** the REF doc following the standard format:\n   ```\n   docs/sop/{TRADE}/REF_{TRADE}_Codes_Standards.md\n   ```\n\n2. **Upload** to database:\n   ```bash\n   python sop_manager.py upload-ref docs/sop/PNT/REF_PNT_Codes_Standards.md\n   ```\n\n3. **Auto-linking**: All SOPs with matching `trade_code` get their `ref_doc_id` updated.\n\n4. **SOP sections** that delegate to the REF doc are marked:\n   - `is_ref_pointer = true`\n   - `ref_section` contains the referenced section name\n\n### REF Pointer Pattern in SOPs\n\n```markdown\n## 3. References & Codes\n\nSee [REF_PNT_Codes_Standards.md](REF_PNT_Codes_Standards.md) — Painting Trade: Codes & Standards Reference.\n```\n\nThis is parsed as:\n- `section_type = \"references\"`\n- `is_ref_pointer = true`\n- `ref_section = \"Painting Trade: Codes & Standards Reference\"`\n\n---\n\n## Dependency Graph\n\nSOPs reference other SOPs in their Scope section to define boundaries:\n\n```markdown\nThis SOP does **not** cover:\n- Exterior trim painting (see PNT-SOP-002: Exterior Siding Painting)\n- Cabinet painting (see PNT-SOP-003: Cabinet Repainting)\n- Drywall repair (see DRW-SOP-001: Drywall Patch Repair)\n```\n\nThese are extracted as `sop_dependencies` records with `link_type = \"cross_reference\"`.\n\n### Dependency Graph Query\n\n```sql\n-- Get all dependencies for an SOP\nSELECT\n  f.sop_number AS from_sop,\n  t.sop_number AS to_sop,\n  t.task_name,\n  d.link_type,\n  d.condition_note\nFROM sop_dependencies d\nJOIN sops f ON d.from_sop_id = f.id\nJOIN sops t ON d.to_sop_id = t.id\nWHERE f.sop_number = \'PNT-SOP-001\';\n```\n\n### Mermaid Visualization\n\n```sql\n-- Generate Mermaid graph\nSELECT \'graph LR\' AS line\nUNION ALL\nSELECT f.sop_number || \' --> \' || t.sop_number\nFROM sop_dependencies d\nJOIN sops f ON d.from_sop_id = f.id\nJOIN sops t ON d.to_sop_id = t.id;\n```\n\n---\n\n## Work Order Integration\n\nSOPs integrate with Work Orders through the step progress tracking system:\n\n```\nSOP (Knowledge)          Work Order (Execution)         Timesheet (Reporting)\n┌──────────────┐         ┌──────────────────┐           ┌──────────────┐\n│ sop_steps    │────────►│ wo_step_progress │──────────►│ timesheet    │\n│              │         │                  │           │ entries      │\n│ phase_name   │         │ status           │           │              │\n│ step_name    │         │ duration_minutes │           │ duration     │\n│ tasks_summary│         │ completed_by     │           │ task_ref     │\n└──────────────┘         └──────────────────┘           └──────────────┘\n```\n\n### Integration Pattern\n\n1. **Template Level**: WO template references `sop_id`\n2. **Creation**: When WO is created, steps are initialized from `sop_steps`\n3. **Execution**: Workers update `work_order_step_progress` per step\n4. **Reporting**: Duration data flows to timesheet entries\n\n### API Endpoints\n\n| Method | Endpoint | Description |\n|---|---|---|\n| `GET` | `/api/sops` | List all SOPs |\n| `GET` | `/api/sops/:id` | Get SOP with sections and steps |\n| `GET` | `/api/templates/:id/sop` | Resolve SOP through template inheritance |\n| `GET` | `/api/work-orders/:id/step-progress` | Get step progress for a WO |\n| `POST` | `/api/work-orders/:id/initialize-steps` | Initialize steps from SOP |\n| `PATCH` | `/api/work-orders/step-progress/:id` | Update step status/duration |\n\n---\n\n## Section Type Classification\n\nThe parser classifies section titles into types using keyword matching:\n\n| Title Pattern | Section Type |\n|---|---|\n| Purpose | `purpose` |\n| Scope | `scope` |\n| References & Codes | `references` |\n| Personnel & Qualifications | `personnel` |\n| Safety Requirements | `safety` |\n| Tools & Equipment | `tools` |\n| Pre-Work Assessment / Pre-Installation | `pre_work` |\n| Procedure — {Phase Name} | `procedure` |\n| Recommended Videos | `videos` |\n| Testing & Commissioning | `testing` |\n| Cleanup & Closeout | `cleanup` |\n| Troubleshooting | `troubleshooting` |\n| Quality Standards | `quality` |\n| Revision History | `revision_history` |\n\n---\n\n## File Structure\n\n```\nskills/sop_library_manager/\n├── SKILL.md              # Skill metadata and instructions\n├── AGENT_GUIDE.md        # Quick reference for agents\n├── README.md             # This file — full documentation\n└── scripts/\n    └── sop_manager.py    # Main CLI/library script\n```\n\n---\n\n## Configuration\n\nEnvironment variables (defaults for local Supabase):\n\n```bash\nSUPABASE_URL=http://host.docker.internal:54321\nSUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY=eyJhbGci...  # local dev key\n```\n\nStorage bucket: `apps` → prefix: `voicelog/sops/`\n\n---\n\n## Idempotency\n\nAll sync operations use a **delete + insert** pattern:\n\n1. Delete existing child records (steps first, then sections — respects FK order)\n2. Insert fresh parsed data\n3. Return counts for verification\n\nThis ensures re-running sync produces identical results regardless of prior state.\n\nThe `upload` command also syncs to the new schema and extracts dependencies automatically.\n'''\n\noutpath = '/a0/usr/projects/timesheet_app/voicelog-scaffold/skills/sop_library_manager/README.md'\nwith open(outpath, 'w') as f:\n    f.write(readme)\n\nimport os\nprint(f'Written {os.path.getsize(outpath)} bytes to {outpath}')\nprint(f'Line count: {len(readme.splitlines())}')"
